<p id="Par29" class="p">Second, to determine whether the monthly soil temperatures evolve as a sinusoidal cycle, we first fitted the 12 months to a sine curve as Eq. [
 <xref rid="Equ3" ref-type="" class="xref">3</xref>] using non-linear least squares regression, and then calculated the sum of square error (SSE) after normalizing by amplitude such that the SSE for different depths are comparable:
 <disp-formula id="Equ6" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">6</label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M15" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$${\rm{SSE}} = \mathop {\sum }\limits_{i = 1}^{12} (\frac{{T_i - \hat T_i}}{{\hat A}})^2,$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M16" class="math">
    <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">SSE</mi>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <munderover accent="false" accentunder="false" class="munderover">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mo class="mo"> ∑</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">i</mi>
      <mo class="mo">=</mo>
      <mn class="mn">1</mn>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mn class="mn">12</mn>
     </mrow>
    </munderover>
    <msup class="msup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mo class="mo">(</mo>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mfrac class="mfrac">
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <msub class="msub">
           <mrow class="mrow">
            <mi class="mi">T</mi>
           </mrow>
           <mrow class="mrow">
            <mi class="mi">i</mi>
           </mrow>
          </msub>
          <mo class="mo">-</mo>
          <msub class="msub">
           <mrow class="mrow">
            <mover accent="true" class="mover">
             <mrow class="mrow">
              <mi class="mi">T</mi>
             </mrow>
             <mo class="mo">^</mo>
            </mover>
           </mrow>
           <mrow class="mrow">
            <mi class="mi">i</mi>
           </mrow>
          </msub>
         </mrow>
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mi class="mi">Â</mi>
         </mrow>
        </mfrac>
       </mrow>
       <mo class="mo">)</mo>
      </mrow>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mn class="mn">2</mn>
     </mrow>
    </msup>
    <mo class="mo">,</mo>
   </math>
   <graphic xlink:href="41467_2019_11103_Article_Equ6.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>where 
 <italic class="italic">T</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">i</italic>
 </sub> is the temperature for month 
 <italic class="italic">i</italic>; 
 <inline-formula id="IEq3" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M17" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\hat T_i$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M18" class="math">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mover accent="true" class="mover">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mi class="mi">T</mi>
       </mrow>
       <mo class="mo">^</mo>
      </mover>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">i</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2019_11103_Article_IEq3.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> is the predicted temperature with the fitted sine curve; 
 <inline-formula id="IEq4" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M19" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\hat A$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M20" class="math">
    <mi class="mi">Â</mi>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41467_2019_11103_Article_IEq4.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> is the amplitude of the fitted curve.
</p>
